Colombia’s BVC Rises on Plan for Peru Exchange Merger Vote

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-25T21:02:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/colombia-s-bvc-rises-on-peru-exchange-merger-vote-announcement.html
Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the
operator of the country’s main securities exchange, rose the
most in five months after saying shareholders will vote a merger
with Peru’s Bolsa de Valores de Lima SA on June 16.  The stock rose 3.2 percent in Bogota trading, the most
since December, to 42.3 pesos at 4 p.m. New York time.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
